Package sprouts

Enum Class SingleChange

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<SingleChange>
sprouts.SingleChange
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<SingleChange>, Constable
public enum SingleChange extends Enum<SingleChange>
A set of constants that describe how a property item has changed. So when a property is mutated, like for example through the Var.set(Object) method, then the property will notify its Action listeners of the change through the ValDelegate object passed to the listener. This delegate object will contain a reference to the SingleChange that occurred, which can be used to determine what kind of change occurred and what action to take in response to that change. The SingleChange enum constants are as follows:
  • NONE - No change occurred.
  • TO_NULL_REFERENCE - The item changed from a non-null reference to a null reference.
  • TO_NON_NULL_REFERENCE - The item changed from a null reference to a non-null reference.
  • VALUE - The item changed its value in terms of Object.equals(Object) returning false.
  • ID - The item implements HasId and changed its HasId.id().

  • Enum Constant Details

    • NONE

      public static final SingleChange NONE
      No change occurred. A change event was probably fired manually. Note that this means that the old and the new value are equal in terms of Object.equals(Object), but not necessarily in terms of the two objects being the exact same instance.

    • TO_NULL_REFERENCE

      public static final SingleChange TO_NULL_REFERENCE
      The item changed from a non-null reference to a null reference.

    • TO_NON_NULL_REFERENCE

      public static final SingleChange TO_NON_NULL_REFERENCE
      The item changed from a null reference to a non-null reference.

    • VALUE

      public static final SingleChange VALUE
      The item changed its value in terms of Object.equals(Object) returning false between the old and new value.

    • ID

      public static final SingleChange ID
      The item implements HasId and changed its HasId.id(). Note that this will never be the case if the item is not an instance of HasId. This is because Sprouts assumes all its items to be value objects by default. So if Object.equals(Object) returns true, but == returns false, then the item is considered to not have changed its identity!

    • of

      public static <T> SingleChange of(Class<T> type, @Nullable T newValue, @Nullable T oldValue)
      Determines the type of change between two supplied values of type T. depending on the supplied values the following constants with their respective meanings may be returned:
      • NONE - No change occurred, the values are equal.
      • TO_NULL_REFERENCE - The item changed from a non-null reference to a null reference.
      • TO_NON_NULL_REFERENCE - The item changed from a null reference to a non-null reference.
      • VALUE - The item changed its value in terms of Object.equals(Object) returning false.
      • ID - The item implements HasId and changed its HasId.id().
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of both values to compare.
      Parameters:
      type - The common type Class of the two supplied values.
      newValue - The new value, which is interpreted as the successor to the oldValue.
      oldValue - The old value, which is interpreted as the predecessor to the oldValue.
      Returns:
      A SingleChange describing how the old value changed to the new one.
